description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Consultant for Community Equipment 60140 SSHE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;County Hall, Norwich&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£36,681 to £40,875 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Temporary contract to cover maternity leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Integrated Community Equipment Service (ICES) is a partnership arrangement covering Norfolk and Suffolk County Council, Norfolk and Waveney CCG and community and acute health providers, delivering equipment to service users in Norfolk and Waveney.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly focused, resourceful and effective Clinician to provide support to the existing ICES team. You will work alongside the Business Manager to help continue the service’s success, maintaining productive relationships and continually driving for efficiencies and more effective equipment solutions. Though working autonomously, the role will have regular contact with Norfolk County Council’s Principal Occupational Therapist to discuss operational and wider system issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be organised, flexible, and calm under pressure, able to work to tight timescales and be confident dealing with changing priorities as well as being able demonstrate the following skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Excellent customer service and communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong organisational skills in a fast-paced environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Good problem solving and decision-making skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Team working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Cultural awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Professional conduct and an ability to manage sensitive information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Friendly and Approachable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have previous experience in a clinical role within a health or social care setting. You will be an excellent communicator and have experience of giving information and advice to professionals via email and by telephone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed to delivering first class levels of support, are positive, and a committed team member with a proactive approach, then we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion regarding this vacancy please contact Andy Dyer ICES Business Manager on 01603 224177 or Faye Gower-Smith Principal Occupational Therapist on 07450742871.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, although currently able to undertake this role remotely, it is predominantly based at the equipment provider’s depot in Norwich.&lt;/p&gt;
